<dl id="n11130i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11130i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11130i"> 130(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> covered with / pall tome</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cependant Am&eacute;lie n&apos;avait point encore prononc&eacute; ses voeux; et pour mourir au monde, il fallait qu&apos;lle pass&acirc;t &agrave; travers le tombeau. Ma soeur se couce sur le marbre; on &eacute;tend sur elle un drap moruaire; quatre flambeaux en marquent les coins. Le pr&ecirc;tre, l&apos;&eacute;tole au cou, le livre &agrave; la main, commence l&apos;Office des morts; de jeunes vierges le continuent. <br><font color="green">[However, Amelie had not yet pronounced her vows; and to die in the world, one has to pass through the tomb. My sister lies on the marble; a morgue sheet is spread over her; four torches mark the corners. The priest, the stole on his neck, the book in his hand, begins the Office of the Dead; young virgins continue it.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Ren&eacute;</i> 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
